RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO $2,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. Texas Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DISCOVERY PEAK was well rated along the inside throughout the first half, then stared bid around the far bend, rallied in the early stretch to close fastest down the lane and was up at the wire. PERFECT TOM stalked the pace while two wide, then gained command at then top of the far turn, was in a long drive down the home stretch but was caught at the end and was second best. MAN IN THE MIDDLE chased the pace from the inside, was urging strongly on the far turn to menace in the stretch and held the show prize in the end. SEEKING CHROME set the pace down the backstretch, was in a long drive heading into the far turn, was headed by an outside rival, vied for the lead heading into the early stretch then gave way in the end. DIXIE MOONSHINE settled in the two path then made a mild bid on the far turn and into the stretch but needed more in the end. BAJA BOOGIE raced two to three wide down the backstretch, then bid on the far turn and did not rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvisable by manageme nt to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CINNAMON FACE stalked the leader from the rail through the first turn and down the backside, loomed up turning for home, took command while angling out around the tiring front-runner, drifted further out two paths bumping PRINESS VOODOO and crowding SHEZA SHINING STAR, was straightened away and drew clear to the wire. PRINCESS VOODOO reserved off the pace while racing along the fence to the far turn, followed the winner along the rail to upper stretch, angled out to the five path , was making up ground when CINNAMON FACE came out several lanes to bump her and cause her to crowd rivals to her outside, was taken up and dropped inside the winner to finish up well as second best. OIL N CANDY unhurried for the first three quarters, was set down for the drive leaving the quarter pole, found a seem in the three path when the winner drifted out and closed well to be coming late. GLORY O sped off to a clear lead in the first turn, set rapid fractions for the first three-quarters and faltered in upper stretch. MYLITTLEWISKEYGIRL settled in hand to race near the rear of the field for the first half mile, circled five wide with a bold move in the far turn and finished evenly while herded in the lane. SHEZA SHINING STAR tracked the pace for the first half, was set to an early drive between horses entering the far turn, rallied from four wide in upper stretch and was squeezed between horses in upper stretch when the winner came out, was taken in hand and finished up evenly to the wire. CHARMING LEAH went evenly and never menaced. TIZ A KNOCKOUT trailed most of the way as a non-factor. DICE ARM sped up to prompt the pace into the first turn, continued to be well placed three wide down the backside, came up empty into the turn and dropped back. THE RIDERS OF SHEZA SHINING STAR AND PRINCESS VOODOO CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE WINNER FOR INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH RUN, UPON REVIEW THE STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED THE WINNER AND PLACED HER SIXTH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $1,675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY LITTLE PRINCE settled in hand to be well rated off the dueling pacesetters, saved ground the entire trip along the rail, cut the corner and closed willingly along the fence to draw clear. GRAMI'S BOY stalked the pace from five wide down the backside, rallied up from four wide to take the lead in upper stretch, failed to change leads down the lane and drifted out to the fifteen path while still keeping momentum and held the place. FORT HOOD sped to battle for the lead from three wide, continued to duel on the pace from between horses to the head of the lane and kept on the only survivor of the front-runners. WINGS FOR ENO chased the leaders down the backside, rallied from four wide turning for home, failed to gain on the top three and passed the tiring pacesetters in the lane. MORO OUTLAW pressed the pace from between horses to upper stretch and weakened coming home. VILLAGE WAY sped up the fence to duel on the lead for a half mile and gave way down the lane. BLING MOUNTAIN raced near the rear of the field and never menaced while making up some ground in the stretch. SHANGHAI GOLD went evenly and was never a threat. SUPREME CAPO raced prominently on the far out side in the early going and faded. GREYSTOKE trailed throughout as a non-factor.
